<h4 class="section-title"><Icon Name="star" /> Watchlist vs. Exclude filters</h4>
<p>These are opposites, both on the <a href="settings">Settings</a> page:</p>
<ul class="mb-4">
    <li><strong>Watchlist</strong> — keywords you <em>do</em> care about. Matching items get a ⭐ and can trigger a desktop notification.</li>
    <li><strong>Exclude filters</strong> — the opposite: matching items are hidden from the News Feed entirely. Plain text or a regex pattern.</li>
</ul>

<h4 class="section-title"><Icon Name="bell" /> Notifications</h4>
<p class="mb-4">
    A background check runs periodically (every 15 minutes by default) looking for new tool/model releases and watchlist
    matches, and can raise a desktop notification via your browser — enable it once on the <a href="settings">Settings</a> page.
    Notifications only fire for items published <em>after</em> the app's first check, so nothing shows in the first few
    minutes after a restart even when everything's working correctly. Click the 🔔 bell icon (top-right, any page) to see
    recent alerts.
</p>

<h4 class="section-title"><Icon Name="database" /> How sources work</h4>
<ul class="mb-4">
    <li>Most sources are plain RSS/Atom feeds, fetched and refreshed automatically.</li>
    <li>Some sources have no title per item (Mastodon posts, for example) — AiPulse shows the start of the post text instead, rather than a blank "(untitled)".</li>
    <li>When the same story is covered by multiple sources, they're merged into one card badged "+N more sources" instead of repeating.</li>
    <li>An admin can flag a source to fetch the <strong>full article text</strong> (not just the teaser) or to <strong>scrape a page with no RSS feed at all</strong> — both configured from the <a href="sources">Sources</a> page.</li>
</ul>

<h4 class="section-title"><Icon Name="graduation-cap" /> Learn more</h4>
<p class="mb-0">
    This covers day-to-day use. For self-hosting details (installing, configuring sources, security, backups),
    see the <a href="https://github.com/Druvo/AiPulse#readme" target="_blank" rel="noopener">project README on GitHub</a>.
</p>
